1. Installation Summary

Installed Windows Server 2019 (Desktop Experience) in VirtualBox. Configured admin password, hostname, and IP settings.

2. Configuration Details

Hostname: SRV-LAB01

IP: 192.168.1.10

Subnet: 255.255.255.0

Gateway: 192.168.1.1

DNS: 8.8.8.8

Remote Desktop: Enabled

3. Verification

System boots correctly with Desktop Experience

Server Manager opens automatically

RDP and network connectivity confirmed via ping

Screenshots attached

4. Reflection

This lab taught me how to install and configure a baseline Windows Server 2019 system, assign static network settings, and prepare for remote management. It helped me understand how on-prem servers are initially configured before domain setup.
